# [IOTOPS](../wg/iotops.html)

## Summary

The IOTOPS working group met at IETF 126. The session was chaired by Alexey Melnikov and Henk Birkholz. The meeting covered updates to active working group drafts, proposed extensions to the Manufacturer Usage Description (MUD) framework, guidelines for IoT DNS security and privacy, and research on DNS privacy enhancements for constrained IoT devices.

Key outcomes included planning a Working Group Last Call (WGLC) for `draft-ietf-iotops-ol`, coordinating collaboration on updating the IoT DNS guidelines (`draft-ietf-iotops-iot-dns-guidelines`), and soliciting mailing list feedback on updating the expired security-enabling technologies summary draft.

