### 2. MUD Extensions and Clarifications
* **Presenter**: Eliot Lear
* **Slides**: [MUD extensions and clarifications](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-iotops-mud-extensions-and-clarifications-00)

Eliot Lear introduced a proposal to update RFC 8520 to resolve known operational issues with Manufacturer Usage Descriptions (MUD). Key points of the proposed draft include:
* **IP Addresses**: Acknowledging that while MUD files should ideally remain stable, many IoT devices hardcode IP addresses, and the model must support this with clear caveats (e.g., avoiding local subnets).
* **Multicast/Broadcasts**: Clarifying how local versus propagating multicast should be flagged, handling normal broadcasts, and addressing the use of directed broadcasts.
* **Collaboration**: Eliot Lear suggested adopting this work and requested volunteers to co-author and refine the document on the list leading up to IETF 127. 

Henk Birkholz noted that providing clear, simplified guides on how to generate MUD files is highly valuable. Eliot Lear recommended [mudmaker.org](https://mudmaker.org) as an accessible starting point.

